        <h3 class='process-head'>Version 2</h3>
        <p>
            After running with that design for a little while, though functional, it didn’t deliver the degree of sleekness I wanted. 
            I felt that the balance of spacing could be improved, along with additional features to give it more style. 
        </p>
        <p>
            Having used animated text effects and parallax effect (where the foreground and background move at different speeds when scrolling) I decided to spice things up by including them. 
            Although something can be said for minimal effects and static design, I also wanted to demonstrate my abilities to incorporate them elegantly into my designs.
        </p>
        <p>
            Giving the content even more opportunity to breathe, I designated a new section explicitly for navigation. 
            In this section, I included the parallax effect, by creating a background design showing connected dots. 
            This was a deliberate representation to show that I’m a problem-solver–I connect dots.
        </p>
