        <p>
            The last dramatic change I decided to add was a sleeker drop down menu for my portfolio. 
            As mentioned, I initially coded a menu in JavaScript as a simple menu. 
            Like most features in my first iteration, it was functional, but lacked any sort of flair. 
            I had used JQuery on another project that required a drop down menu that would work perfectly for this function.
        </p>
        <p>
            Along with the change in the menu, I decided to update the gallery display of the images, as well. 
            I used a sharper, more professional looking display that allowed for keyboard navigation (arrows and escape key). 
            From a user’s standpoint, the previous display was lacking in elegance–in both form and function. In the update, I also removed the captions, except when the image has been clicked. 
            I wanted to bring as much focus on the images themselves, so I increased their size, as well as displayed them each on their own line (as opposed to two side by side).
        </p>
